AGI - North Korean leader Kim Jong-un presented a building plan to expand the capital Pyongyang> to the east and promised to renew some of the billing areas, as state media reported. Kim announced the plan during the opening ceremony on Sunday, in which he presented the beginning of the construction of 10,000 apartments in the Hwasong area of Pyongyang, as part of a larger development plan that will lead to the construction of about 50,000 housing units in the capital, today reported the state press agency KCNA.
&nbsp;
During the opening speech, Kim stated that his country will follow a building plan to expand the capital's roads eastward, towards Kangdong County, after completing the Hwasong construction project. According to the plan, in Hwasong and in the nearby areas there will also be a series of scientific research centers, schools and modern housing units, creating another scientific and cultural district within the city.> According to the five-year plan presented in 2021, Kim committed to building 10,000 units each year.&nbsp;

